indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Presently, Ofsted are planning a new recruitment campaign</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, and, assurance</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> given that ‘we will make every eff</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ort to ensure that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">we attract gifted and talented BME head teachers and college principals’ (</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Lorraine Langham. Chief Operating Officer Ofsted, to M. Cosh 21/10/13).However, to ‘restrict’ recruitment to just BME head teachers and college principals is, is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">my opinion, a flawed policy. There are other BME personnel within the UK education system, who are well qualified/able to be considered by Ofsted for HMI appointment, but, for varying reasons, do not qualify for the present/proposed Ofsted selection criter</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ia for BME HMI.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">As a Central London resident, now retired, but, with a past career in education, I am of the firm opinion that the present lack of BME HMI has an indelible and adverse influence on the career aspirations of BME personnel here in the United </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Kingdom.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Also, as a lo</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ng serving school Governor </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">within Central London, it has been my experience that many BME pupils and their parents/guardians perceive the lack of any BME HMI within visiting Ofsted Inspection Teams as oppressive.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">For whatever reason, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">my past endeavour to engage various BME individuals within our public sphere, and also, within major UK BME organisations about the lack of BME Ofted HMI, and, the implications, I have been unsuccessful. This inaction I subscribe to impotence more than dis</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">interest. This lack of interest/concern I have experienced at firsthand within my own home Labour controlled Borough of Islington</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, where I have challenged the Council for a number of years</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">as to why they have allowed the Leadership Team of our Education Se</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">rvice (CE Islington/Mott Macdonald) to be void of any BME personnel. This fact, in our diverse/multi cultural Borough, I consider to be reprehensible.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I therefore req</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">uest that the Education Committee </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">challenge Sir Michael and his Team about BME HMI appoint</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ment/recruitment, and, suggest that they take more/outside advice on the matter.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-si